### Main result

Local concavity is admissible only if the induced stochastic liquidity process does not violate the no-manipulation bound.

### Interpretation

Concavity alone is not enough. The way concavity interacts with market activity and liquidity changes matters.

The trader must check that the reduced-form stochastic liquidity path does not imply artificial round-trip profits.

